Pastor Enoch Adeboye, the General Overseer of the Redeemed Christian Church of God (RCCG) on Tuesday met with Kaduna State Governor, Nasir El-Rufai. The meeting was held at the Sir Kashim Ibrahim Government House in Kaduna. Adeboye made the trip days after eight kidnapped RCCG adherents from Kaduna Province 1, were freed. The Region 30, Trinity Sanctuary members were abducted on March 26 along Kachia-Kafanchan road while travelling in a church bus. The cleric predicted that Nigeria will record victory in its battle against insecurity. “The Almighty God is going to fight for Kaduna State, He is going to fight for Nigeria”, Adeboye prayed.